most_relevant.description:
I had a very disappointing experience and the behavior of the owner was shockingly unprofessional.

About 15 days ago, my friend and I visited the restaurant. It wasn’t busy at the time, and we ordered a half plate of a veg dish, some Indian bread, and daal. Although we were served a half portion, we were charged nearly 70% of the full plate price. Still, we didn’t complain and paid without raising any issue.

Today, we visited again and ordered the same items. This time, the place was a bit more crowded (about 10 customers). After waiting for 20–25 minutes, instead of food, a worker came and informed us that they wouldn’t be serving half plates. When we went to the counter to ask why, the owner arrogantly said:

“That day I had fewer customers, so I fulfilled it. Today I have many (आज कस्टमर हैं), so it’s not possible.”

This clearly shows a greedy and opportunistic attitude — serving smaller orders only when business is slow, and refusing them when there’s more profit to be made elsewhere. It was insulting to be treated as unworthy of basic service just because other customers might be ordering more.

I was extremely disappointed, not just by the inconsistent policy, but more by the owner's rude and dismissive tone. Customer loyalty means nothing here, and it’s obvious the focus is purely on making money — not on providing fair service.
I am wishing this restaurant the emptiness I had encountered the first time. So that owner learns a lesson about humility and value of customers.

I once visited here in 2022. Fusion Tadka in Bhilai is a good budget-friendly option, especially for group outings. The infrastructure is decent, but what truly stands out is the long seating arrangement — something many popular restaurants often lack. It’s a convenient spot for group celebrations or casual get-togethers.

The food quality is quite good for the price. While it may not exceed expectations, it certainly delivers value, and you’re unlikely to leave disappointed.

Fusion Tadka, Bhilai: A Flavorful Experience

Food:
The food at Fusion Tadka was flavorful, with generous helpings of garlic and onion. However, as someone who doesn't enjoy overly spicy dishes, I found it a bit intense. Hence, I'm giving it three stars.

Atmosphere and Ambience:
The outside seating area had a charming village theme, which added to the overall appeal. Good vibes all around!
But inside a bit closed appearance.

Service:
Despite being the only customer on a rainy day, the staff treated me well. Prompt service and a friendly demeanor.

most_relevant.description:
We recently dined at Highway Vegetarian Family Restaurant and had an exceptional experience! The restaurant's ambiance is warm and inviting, perfect for a family outing.

We ordered a mix of South Indian and Chinese dishes, and each item was expertly prepared and presented. The flavors were rich and authentic, and the portion sizes were generous.

What impressed us most was the reasonable pricing - great taste doesn't have to break the bank! The service was also prompt and courteous.

Overall, Highway Vegetarian Family Restaurant is a must-visit for vegetarians and foodies alike. We can't wait to go back and try more of their delicious dishes!

Our family has been loyal customers of this restaurant since its inception — it once stood out for its exceptional food, warm service, and genuine hospitality. Every visit used to feel special, filled with care and consistency that kept us coming back for years.

Sadly, that charm has completely faded. The food quality has dropped, the service feels indifferent, and the passion that once defined this place is gone. The owner now seems interested only in collecting the day’s earnings rather than reviving what was once a beloved dining spot. It’s disheartening to see a restaurant we cherished now struggling to breathe its last.

The Highway Restaurant has been a staple in Power House Bhilai for many years. I remember my father taking us there as he loved the Special Sambar Vada, and I enjoy it just as much, along with my daughter. The taste has remained consistent over the years. I have been visiting this place for the past 40 years. They also offer a vegetarian thali and indidvidual curries as à la carte options. We tried Veg Crispy Dosa, Masala Dosa, Paneer Dosa, Cheese Dosa, Idli Sambar, Sambar Vada, and Uttapam. Although there are many new eateries in Bhilai now, this restaurant still possesses its own charm and continues to thrive.

most_relevant.description:
Pizza Hut ..... The name says it all. Once I was the biggest fan of its pizza but don't know why it's losing on footfall, maybe home delivery is picking up.
Food is standard and good, as always.
Service is good and staff is courteous but I'm always confused whether they serve on table or we've to take from counter and it depends on the person on desk. Baked pasta tried for first time and tasted good.
The atmosphere is bit suffocating due to lack of air or proper AC. The reason quoted was AC is common for Mall, then why it's not the same suffocation in every shop, it's unanswered.
When there's rush you've to ask for table cleaning but when there's only one family still floor is not clean so there reluctance on this front that needs improvement.
Rest all is perfect.

I am writing to share my recent experience at your Bhilai Surya Mall branch, which unfortunately was very disappointing.

I had ordered two different flavours – one medium and one small – but both turned out to be the same flavour. In the medium cheese corn, the corn and cheese were not up to the mark, and the second order was exactly the same. This made me question the point of ordering separately. It felt like a complete waste, and I felt misled.

In addition, for the fries and garlic bread, there was no proper dip or sauce provided – only regular red sauce. When I asked for sauce, I was simply given the table red sauce. This is unlike my experience in Raipur, where not only was the food better, but the staff behaviour was also more courteous.

Moreover, I noticed that this branch does not even have a washroom facility, which is very inconvenient for customers.

Overall, my visit felt like a total waste of money. I usually never give feedback, but today I am compelled to do so because I am truly disappointed. I had brought my brother here for a treat with great excitement, but the entire experience was ruined.
Everything was great(food and ambience) except there was no washroom......do provide basic amenities
